\frac{4}{5}
BD=\sqrt{BC^2+AB^2}=\sqrt{30^2+40^2}=50
 \frac{AB}{BD}=\frac{40}{50}=\frac{4}{5} 
AE=\frac{4}{5}\times 30=24 \;\;\; \text{ and }\;\;\; EB=\frac{4}{5}\times DC=\frac{4}{5}\times40=32
\text{Area}=\frac{1}{2}\times 32\times 24=384
